arch:property.oc:show_val: Arbitrary spit in the midden at the side of building 3, very similar in composition to the other units, 8143, 8159 and 8178. A low percentage of the bone has been burnt, digested bone is present but its frequency is not as great as in 8178 or 8159. Species present are sheep/goat and a mandible of a very small carnivore that was separated as microfauna. There was also a point made out of a sheep ulna. {Not a tool; NR 2001.} A cattle metatarsal came from the dry sieve. 4mm flotation sample # 12 was recorded for diagnostics only. Last number = 137

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
